  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable &amp; Equitable Wealth Creation in Amuria (SEWCA)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of the &quot;Sustainable and Equitable Wealth Creation in Amuria&quot; project is to ensure target groups in selected sub-counties of Amuria have improved food security, diversified sources of income and enhanced interactions with markets.

The expected results from this project are:                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Output 1:Target groups achieve significantly increased agricultural production contributing to improved food security 
Output 2:Target groups have diversified sources of income from on-farm and off-farm activities. 
Output 3: Target groups are benefiting from effective linkages with market supply and value chains. 
Output 4: Reduced negative impact of HIV &amp;amp; AIDS, gender inequalities and disasters as a result of partners embedding mainstreaming approaches in their organizations and modalities of work 
Output 5: Mechanisms in place for the two way flow of information between the target groups and other peace building initiatives and networks which would influence decision and policy making specific to security, humanitarian protection and recovery in Amuria</narrative>
  </description>
